				{
					"type": "item",
					"name": "minecraft:written_book",
					"functions": [
						{
							"function": "set_book_contents",
							"author": "Choascraft",
							"title": "Captain of the Unknown",
							"pages": [
								"Day 1\n\nThe crew celebrates tonight. Gold, glory, and forgotten treasure await beyond the western sea.",
								"Day 4\n\nThe ocean grows colder. No birds follow us now. Even the waves sound hollow.",
								"Day 7\n\nElias claims he saw lights beneath the ship last night. Green lights moving in the deep.",
								"Day 10\n\nWe crossed into black water today. The sea below reflects no moonlight.",
								"Day 12\n\nFirst sailor missing. No scream. No blood. Only wet footprints leading overboard.",
								"Day 14\n\nThe men whisper of the Black Trench. Ancient sailors feared this place long before us.",
								"Day 16\n\nRotting sharks circle the hull at all hours. Their flesh hangs loose yet they still hunt.",
								"Day 18\n\nNone aboard sleep peacefully now. Something scratches beneath the lower deck at night.",
								"Day 20\n\nA storm struck without warning. One supply ship vanished beneath the waves entirely.",
								"Day 22\n\nFood rationing begins tomorrow. Morale weakens faster than the hull.",
								"Day 24\n\nThe cook caught two sailors fighting over dried fish. One lost an eye.",
								"Day 26\n\nI saw movement beneath the water larger than any whale known to man.",
								"Day 27\n\nDead orcas followed us through the fog tonight. Their eyes glowed pale white.",
								"Day 28\n\nOne of the crew swore the sea itself spoke his name before he vanished.",
								"Day 29\n\nWe found ruins below the trench waters. Stone towers covered in coral and bone.",
								"Day 30\n\nTreasure litters the ruins. Gold fused into coral like flesh growing around metal.",
								"Day 31\n\nThe men grow greedy despite starvation. Some refuse to leave the ruins behind.",
								"Day 32\n\nA sailor named Briggs was dragged overboard by something massive beneath the wrecks.",
								"Day 33\n\nWe crafted new armor from trench metals and coral plating. Heavy... but strong.",
								"Day 34\n\nThe sea groans at night now. Not waves. Something deeper.",
								"Day 35\n\nThree crewmen vanished below deck. We found only seawater and blood.",
								"Day 36\n\nI saw the trench open tonight.\n\nNot a canyon...\nA mouth.",
								"Day 37\n\nThe Abyss Leviathan surfaced beside the fleet. Its eye alone dwarfed our ship.",
								"Day 38\n\nMen jumped into the sea rather than face it. The sharks devoured them instantly.",
								"Day 39\n\nThe undead orcas rammed the hull while the leviathan circled beneath us.",
								"Day 40\n\nHalf the fleet is gone. Fire burns atop black water.",
								"Day 41\n\nThe crew mutinied at dawn. Hunger and fear have made beasts of us all.",
								"Day 42\n\nI put on the Sunking Armor tonight. The metal feels alive against my skin.",
								"Day 43\n\nWe harpooned the leviathan. It did nothing.\n\nGod help us... it did nothing.",
								"Day 44\n\nThe beast struck the hull at sunset. The sea erupted around us.",
								"Day 45\n\nThe lower deck floods. Men scream below me while something tears through the ship.",
								"Day 46\n\nI can hear breathing beneath the floorboards.",
								"Day 47\n\nThe trench is opening.\nThe sea itself is moving.",
								"Final Entry\n\nI thought we were hunting the abyss.\n\nBut the abyss was waiting for us."
							]
						}
					]
				}
			]
		}
	]
}
